<section xml:id="sec-intersecting-secants-and-tangents">
  <title>Intersecting Secants and Tangents</title>

  <!-- Content summary: - Explain what a secant is - Detail how, when two secant segments are drawn to a circle from an exterior point, the product of one full secant and its external portion equals the product of the other. - Highlight the specific case where a tangent and a secant meet at an external point. The square of the tangent segment equals the product of the whole secant and its external part.( Tangent-Secant Theorem) - Highlight that tangent segments to a circle from the same external point are congruent (equal in length). -->

